Hi - just read the problem and couldn't stop thinking.. So I've implemented it in FORTH, probably the most natural way of expressing a program's flow. I kept it functional instead of optimizing it - after all, it executes about 500 times / second now. If you don't yet have it on your PC, apt-get install gforth (or download the .exe for windows).
: ?DIVISIBLE ( prefix n -- prefix n flag ) is prefix divisible by n? 2dup MOD 0= ;
: _?NEW# ( prefix n -- flag ) does prefix contain n?, destructive over 0= IF 2drop -1 ELSE over 10 MOD over - 0= IF 2drop 0 ELSE swap 10 / swap RECURSE THEN THEN ;
: ?NEW# ( prefix n -- prefix n flag ) does prefix contain n? 2DUP _?NEW# ;
: DIGITS ( prefix n -- ) loop: number starting with prefix and has n digits dup 10 = IF drop . ELSE 10 1 DO over 10 * i ?NEW# IF + over ?DIVISIBLE IF 1+ RECURSE ELSE 2drop THEN ELSE 2drop THEN LOOP 2drop THEN ;
: 9DIGITS ( -- ) solve the 9-digits problem 0 0 1 DIGITS ;
9DIGITS BYE
